===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かささぎ}}
[[File:Common Magpie (Pica pica).JPG|thumb|right|250px|{{m|ja||鵲|tr=kasasagi}}: a '''Eurasian magpie''']]
{{wp|ja:カササギ}}
{{wp|Eurasian magpie}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=かささき|-}}, first appears in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

Derivation {{unk|ja|nocap=y}}, theories include:
* The initial ''kasa-'' may be cognate with or a borrowing from an earlier form of {{cog|ko|까치||[[magpie]]}}.
* The final ''-sagi'' may be a reference to the white chest, alluding to the similar plumage of certain kinds of {{m|ja|鷺|tr=sagi||[[heron]], [[egret]]}}.
* Alternatively, the final ''-sagi'' may derive from [[onomatopoeia]], imitative of the bird's call.
* May be a corruption of {{m|ja|烏|tr=karasu||[[crow]]}} + {{m|ja||鷺|tr=sagi|[[heron]], [[egret]]}}:
*: {{IPAchar|/karasu saɡi/}} → *{{IPAchar|/kasːaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kasasaɡi/}}
* May be a corruption of {{m|ja|カラ|tr=kara||pos=onomatopoeia for [[caw]]ing, seen in {{m|ja|烏|tr=karasu}}, “[[crow]]”}} + {{m|ja|鷦鷯|tr=sasagi||[[wren]]|pos=obsolete}}:
*: {{IPAchar|/kara sasaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kasasaɡi/}}
* May be a corruption of {{m|ja||カチカチ|tr=kachikachi|pos=onomatopoeia imitative of the bird's call}} + {{m|ja||鷺|tr=sagi|[[heron]], [[egret]]}}:
*: {{IPAchar|/kat͡ɕikat͡ɕi saɡi/}} → *{{IPAchar|/kat̚t͡sasaɡi/}} → {{IPAchar|/kasasaɡi/}}

